	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			For the last couple of weeks my group have been fighting in Solusek's Eye (solusek a, soldunga).  Here's a bit about the dungeon...<BR>
<BR>
From what we've seen so far the dungeon is perfect for a mid 20's group.  There are many loot dropping named's and the regular goblins carry fine steel and a bit of plat quite often.  Also the dungeon is usually quite empty.  Especially when you compare it to Unrest.  (this is the case on Brell Serilis anyway).<BR>
<BR>
We have explored most all of the dungeon except for anything behind the door to the Goblin castle (the Goblin King area).  Most of the goblins we've run into range from 20 to 25ish.  Some of the named's that we ran into were red, but handled by our party.<BR>
<BR>
Our first trips consisted of moving our party away from the lava filled entrance and into a good pull room.  This is a room near the zone line to sol b so if you got in trouble with the gob's you could zone into sol b (usually there is nothing at the zone line, but we had to recover a corpse once, solb is 35+...).  To get here go into the little whole in the wall down the first flight of stairs from the entrance.  Then stick to the right past a few goblins and into a roundish room with a path down.  Follow the path down and you'll hit solb.  The roundish room is a good place to familiarize yourself with level and strength of the various goblins.  There are Young, inferno and flame lines of goblins and include nasty backstabers, mele'ers, shaman and wizards.  In permafrost the healers are quite nasty.  In solusek it's the wizards you will want to target first.  The shaman aren't as bad.  The melee'ers are quite tough as well.  The wizards can burn a level 25 tanks down pretty quick, so load up some stuns and use them.  As in most dungeons running happens so keep the gobs snared/rooted.  We made some great experience just pulling to this safe room from level 22 to 24 and we're doing ok with parties as small as 3 people.  Eventually it was time to move on and explore the rest of the dungeon.<BR>
<BR>
As you head away from the solb/safe area you walk along a long straight path.  To your right is a drop and a door to the entrance to the Goblin stronghold (we haven't explored there yet).  If you continue straight along this path you can find the gnome miner area (and a neat castle) through some passages to the right and many of the dungeons named baddies to the left and straight.  Our first expedition was to the Kobold Predator room.  Along the way you will encounter rooms of mostly 2 or 3 goblins at a time.  This makes it easy for moving through the dungeon, becuase you can knock them down, rest then move on.<BR>
<BR>
The Kobold Predator room is quite easy to hold once you get to it.  It has a large staircase down to an open room (where you can cast ae spells without worry) and only 2 or 3 spawn points.  The predator doesn't seem to show up to often (twice in our 4 or 5 hours in the area), and drops Kobold hide boots (decent boots for casters we got 2) and the obsidian shard.<BR>
<BR>
You can pull goblins to the predator room, but we were burned by some bad pathing one time and ended up doing some corpse recovery so I'd recommend just moving to the fight.<BR>
<BR>
If you travel past the Predator room you come to the Goblin foreman room.  There are 3 or 4 goblins in this room and the Goblin foreman pops as one of them on occasion.  The Foreman drops the foreman tunic (great druid/monk tunic) and is a pretty easy fight.<BR>
<BR>
There are a few other rooms near here as well as some hidden walls and another zone to solb.  One of the rooms contains the spawn point for Singe a fire drake.  Singe roams around and we caught him once or twice.  He dropped a decent belt, the drakescale (or hide) belt both times he also drops some nice earrings.  These 3 spawns are packed closely together and if noone else is in the area you can rake in a lot of good loot and experience in a short ammount of time.  We got 4 or 5 of the named's in just a couple hours, using the predator room as our base.<BR>
<BR>
Beyond these rooms and deeper into the dungeon is the Efretti/Goblin Captain area.  We managed to kill the Efretti once in a particularly nasty battle which ended in a corpse recovery trip.  This area of the dungeon is a bit harder and the maps are not very good, but had we been better prepared we could have handled the battles in this area.  The Efretti dropped platinum armbands (another great druid item) the time we killed him.  We also made the trip back to the captain room again.  Watch out in this area.  Sometimes healers will cast through walls/floors and blazing elementals show up.  The captain drops some nice charred armor.<BR>
<BR>
Close to the Effretti area is an entrance to the Gnome miners area.  This is where the highly priced Charred guardian tunic and sheild come from.  The gnomes are not aggresive to those who are welcomed in Akanon and carry a faction hit with many of the gnomish guilds.  There are gnomish clockworks, miners as well as a merchant and a couple named gnomes (most were red to us at 25).  We have a gnome in our group and were only after the clockwork with the shield so we just explored this area and didn't fight.  There are a few trap bridges which close as you're walking across (dropping you in the lava) so look out for that.<BR>
<BR>
Various clockworks are the placeholder for the clockwork that carries the shield and breastplate.  The one time we killed the EXG was because a friendly passerby informed us that she was there and carrying the shield (you can see it on her).  I had heard horror stories about the clockwork being impervious to magic, and since she was red to us, we were unsure of her level.  We prepared for the fight of our lives, buffing up our tanks and quickening them while even our casters broke out their dragoon dirks to do a little melee'ing.  Well the clockwork wasn't all that.  She went down pretty quick and I'm sure a group of 2 or 3 25ish melee'ers could take her.  We got the shield.<BR>
<BR>
One other note.  Enchanter's in Earth Elemental form and after casting benevolence will have a non KOS faction with the goblins.  This makes corpse recovery easy, however after a bunch of fighting I'm now down to Threatenighly and have to run past the goblins so they don't kill me.  Also the gnomes don't like elemental illusion.  I was passing through the goblin area with it on, then a clockwork knocked me into the lava.  Luckily I found a ledge to hop onto and gated out in time...<BR>
<BR>
Maryinn of the Merry Band <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
  
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
