	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Avoid this zone at all costs if you value your equipment.<BR>
<BR>
This zone is bugged beyond all belief.  As an Ogre, the first problem I had was getting in.  The entranceway is too narrow and it generally takes 3 or 4 attempts to not bounce out of the zone as soon as I enter (with noone else in the zone).  Once inside, other players who enter are generally not seen, including group members.  Zone bugs cause players (and corpses) to be invisible, although you can see the player's spell effects.<BR>
<BR>
Most of the zone is narrow ledges where the group doesn't really fit (even after casting shrink on everyone).  You will bounce off these ledges and fall into the lava, which does 48 damage a couple times a second until you die.  Your corpse will sink to the bottom of the lava, and you will have to petition a GM to get it.  This took 2 days checking every few hours until there was a GM on.<BR>
<BR>
I tried to summon my corpse using levitate above the lava, but sank right in while levitated.  Once you are getting damaged by it, your gate spell will be interrupted.<BR>
<BR>
Some of the bugs in the zone work in your favor.  The pathing problems are unreal.  If you stand in the hallway at the entrance, where you first come out onto the ledge, the goblins passing by cannot see you.  They will just stand there while you nuke them without attacking back.<BR>
<BR>
This dungeon should be removed from the game, but will not be.  Its purpose is quite obviously to keep the &quot;economy&quot; going by causing players to lose all their equipment.  I witnessed 5 other people falling in the lava and not being able to get their corpses while waiting for a GM to recover mine.<BR>
<BR>

			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
