	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Well, I had been hunting this zone for a god bit of time when I was a little younger, and yes, while I have been knocked into the lava once, I have never realy had any equipment loss issues. I was always able to recover my corpse, and my items. There were indeed a few times that my corpse was invisible to me, but other members of my party could see it. If you zone out and in again, generally you will be fine...<BR>
<BR>
This is actually, with a little patience, and some decent planing, an excellent dungeon. While I have died here an unknown amount of times (can you say train?) I still think that it really is one of the best dungeons around. It has decent loot, decent xp, and no shortage of fights. There are several methods that can be used here for hunting, depending on the party configuration. <BR>
<BR>
I will have to return here once again, as I have been gone a while, and in a sick way, I miss it. To those of you who are having troubles here, by all means, take your time.. Eventually you get comfortable with this place, and learn how to work in there.. And if you happen to die,  horrible death in this dungeon..... <BR>
<BR>
.....keep in mind losing experience on your character gains you experience as a player...<BR>
<BR>
Dtreli Eme
